<subSubSection id="C5A66520FFFBFF8AAAF0738BFC59FD3E" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFFBFF8AAAF0738BFC56FE9D" blockId="10.[166,1225,692,943]" lastBlockId="13.[174,1233,175,650]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">
D i a g n o s i s (
<figureCitation id="15872A2EFFFBFF8DABA6738AFDF8FD7B" box="[397,515,692,719]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStart-3="Fig" captionStart-4="Fig" captionStart-5="Fig" captionStart-6="Fig" captionStartId-0="10.[170,201,1696,1718]" captionStartId-1="3.[169,202,1208,1230]" captionStartId-2="4.[162,195,1033,1055]" captionStartId-3="6.[170,203,994,1016]" captionStartId-4="7.[175,208,1630,1652]" captionStartId-5="8.[166,199,1664,1686]" captionStartId-6="11.[170,199,1658,1678]" captionTargetBox-0="[181,1210,978,1670]" captionTargetBox-1="[394,1138,174,1180]" captionTargetBox-2="[189,1213,155,1027]" captionTargetBox-3="[174,1200,175,940]" captionTargetBox-4="[174,758,913,1615]" captionTargetBox-5="[188,1205,892,1628]" captionTargetId-0="figure-298@10.[166,1224,956,1688]" captionTargetId-1="figure-186@3.[389,1146,170,1197]" captionTargetId-2="figure-387@4.[170,1216,155,1031]" captionTargetId-3="figure-280@6.[170,1217,170,968]" captionTargetId-4="figure-501@7.[174,758,913,1616]" captionTargetId-5="figure-333@8.[166,1224,892,1642]" captionTargetId-6="figure-8@11.[174,1232,171,1633]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionTargetPageId-3="6" captionTargetPageId-4="7" captionTargetPageId-5="8" captionTargetPageId-6="11" captionText-0="Fig. 6. Ledomyia olgae, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–3697): 1 — general appearance; 2, 3 — palpi (variability of shape); 4 — flagellomeres 9–11; 5 — flagellomere 5; 6, 7 — genitalia (6 — ventral view,7 — dorsal view).Scale bars 0.1 mm." captionText-1="Fig. 1. Rovnobrachineura kiryeyevi, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–3701): 1 — general appearance; 2 — scape, pedicel, flagellomeres 1–2; 3 — flagellomeres 8–10; 4 — flagellomeres 6–7; 5 — mouth parts and palpi; 6 — genitalia dorsally. Scale bars 0.1 mm." captionText-2="Fig. 2. Brachineura polessica, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–1236): 1 — general appearance; 2 — scape, pedicel, flagellomeres 1–2; 3 — flagellomeres 9–10; 4 — flagellomeres 6–7; 5 — flagellomeres 3–5; 6 — palpus; 7 — middle tarsomeres 3–5; 8 — middle tarsomeres 1–2; 9 — middle tarsomere 1; 10 — middle tarsomere 5; 11 — ovipositor laterally. Scale bars 0.1 mm." captionText-3="Fig. 3. Popovineura nacta, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–666): 1 — general appearance; 2 — scape, pedicel, flagellomeres 1–2; 3 — flagellomeres 5–6; 4 — flagellomeres 8–11; 5 — palpus; 6 — fore tarsus; 7 — fore tarsomere 5; 8 — genitalia. Scale bars 0.1 mm." captionText-4="Fig. 4. Nascensluna mellea, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–1601): 1 — general appearance; 2 — flagellomeres 8–10; 3 — flagellomere 5; 4 — ovipositor. Scale bars 0.1 mm." captionText-5="Fig. 5. Rhizomyia parkalovi, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–7385): 1 — general appearance; 2 — head; 3 — palpus; 4 — flagellomeres 9–10; 5, 6 — tarsomere 1 (variability of shape); 7 — flagellomere 5; 8 — apex of abdomen. Scale bars 0.1 mm." captionText-6="Fig. 7. Rovnobrachineura kiryeyevi, male, holotype SIZK, N K–3701 (1–3); Brachineura polessica, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–1236) (4, 5); Rhizomyia parkalovi, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–7385) (6, 7): 1, 4, 6 — head and antenna (1 — ×129; 4 — ×62; 6 — ×117); 2 — genitalia (×283); 3, 5, 7 — general appearance (3 — ×46; 5 — ×29; 7 — ×39)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452805" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452793" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452795" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452797" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452799" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452801" figureDoi-6="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6462009" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6452805/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6452793/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6452795/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6452797/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6452799/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/6452801/files/figure.png" httpUri-6="https://zenodo.org/record/6462009/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">
fig. 6, 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFBFF8DABF3738BFDF8FD7B" box="[472,515,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">1–7</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="15872A2EFFFBFF8DA83A738BFDDBFD7B" box="[529,544,693,719]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[167,196,1653,1673]" captionTargetId="figure-9@12.[163,1221,171,1625]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 8. Popovineura nacta, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–666) (1, 2); Ledomyia olgae, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–3697) (3, 4); Nascensluna mellea, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–1601) (5–7): 1–3, 7 — general appearance (1 — ×45; 2 — ×38; 3 — ×48; 7 — ×64); 4 — antennae (4 — ×129); 5 — hind leg (×82); 6 — head and antenna (×131)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6462013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6462013/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">8</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFBFF8DA806738BFDA3FD7B" box="[557,600,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">
<figureCitation id="15872A2EFFFBFF8DA806738BFDC6FD7B" box="[557,573,693,719]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[170,203,994,1016]" captionTargetBox="[174,1200,175,940]" captionTargetId="figure-280@6.[170,1217,170,968]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Popovineura nacta, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–666): 1 — general appearance; 2 — scape, pedicel, flagellomeres 1–2; 3 — flagellomeres 5–6; 4 — flagellomeres 8–11; 5 — palpus; 6 — fore tarsus; 7 — fore tarsomere 5; 8 — genitalia. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452797/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="15872A2EFFFBFF8DA861738BFDA3FD7B" box="[586,600,693,719]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[175,208,1630,1652]" captionTargetBox="[174,758,913,1615]" captionTargetId="figure-501@7.[174,758,913,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Nascensluna mellea, female, holotype (SIZK, N K–1601): 1 — general appearance; 2 — flagellomeres 8–10; 3 — flagellomere 5; 4 — ovipositor. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452799" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452799/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">4</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
). Wing, body and legs are conspicuously covered by scales. Antennae are 2+8–12-segmented. Male flagellomeres subcylindrical with neck and swollen basal enlargement. Female flagellomeres elongated, sessile, without neck. Tarsal claws toothed on the forelegs, toothed or simple on the mid- and hindlegs. Palpi are mostly 4-segmented, labrum triangular. Wing is broad, R 
<subScript id="113834EEFFFBFF8DA8D47279FCE1FCE1" attach="left" box="[767,794,839,853]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">1+2</subScript>
joins C before its midlength. R 
<subScript id="113834EEFFFBFF8DAEBD7279FB4AFCE1" attach="left" box="[1174,1201,839,853]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">4+5</subScript>
is straight or curved, joins C rather far before wing apex; C broken at junction with R 
<subScript id="113834EEFFFBFF8DAE567259FB63FCC1" attach="left" box="[1149,1176,871,885]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">4+5</subScript>
; Cu is forked. Genitalia are transversal. Gonocoxites are ovoid or parallel-sided. Gonostylus is short, excavated ventrally, terminated by very wide apical or dorso-apical claw, protruding from dorsal part of gonostylus. Cerci are cordiform with very deep excision. Hypoproct slightly caved. Aedeagus usually equal or longer than gonocoxites. Basal processes of gonocoxites are well developed, strongly narrowed apically. Ovipositor very long, extensible, apically with two terminal lamellae with two small, obtuse spines.
</paragraph>
<caption id="D9C36623FFFBFF8DAA81779EFB45F965" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452805" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452805/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" startId="10.[170,201,1696,1718]" targetBox="[181,1210,978,1670]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFFBFF8DAA81779EFB45F965" blockId="10.[170,1229,1696,1745]" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 6. 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFFBFF8DAACD779EFE89F901" authorityName="Fedotova et Perkovsky" authorityYear="2014" box="[230,370,1696,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ledomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFBFF8DAACD779EFE89F901" box="[230,370,1696,1717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">Ledomyia olgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, holotype (SIZK, N K–3697): 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFBFF8DA893779EFD25F902" box="[696,734,1696,1718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">1 —</emphasis>
general appearance; 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFBFF8DA9B0779EFC5DF901" box="[923,934,1696,1717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">2</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFBFF8DA99B779EFC2DF902" box="[944,982,1696,1718]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">3 —</emphasis>
palpi (variability of shape); 
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFBFF8DAA817785FF4EF964" box="[170,181,1723,1744]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="45">4</emphasis>
