<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFFCFF8AAAC87011FB81FDBD" blockId="13.[174,1233,175,650]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
Species included. The genus is nearly cosmopolitan, two species were described from tropical regions (
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AAB517071FD3BFEDE" author="Fedotova, Z. A. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." box="[378,704,335,362]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 19" refId="ref10138" refString="Fedotova, Z. A., Sidorenko, V. S. Nine new species of genus Ledomyia Kieffer, 1895 (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) from the Russian Far East // Far Eastern Entomologist. - 2007. - 169. - P. 1 - 19." type="book chapter" year="2007">Fedotova, Sidorenko, 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Genus includes 26 species, 17 of them are Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AAB107051FE11FE3D" author="Mamaev, B. M." box="[315,490,367,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" refId="ref10726" refString="Mamaev, B. M. Gall-midges of the USSR. 7. New species of non-gall-making gall midges of the tribe Oligotrophini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) // Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie. - 1967. - 46. - P. 873 - 883. - Russian: Мaмaiv B. М. Gaллitы СССР. 7. Нovыi vidы сvobodнozivuщik gaллit iz tрibы Oligotrophini (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae)." type="book" year="1967">Mamaev, 1967</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AABD87051FD52FE3D" author="Skuhrava, M." box="[499,681,367,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="71 - 204" refId="ref11457" refString="Skuhrava, M. Family Cecidomyiidae // Contributions to a Manual of Palaearctic Diptera (with Special Reference to Flies of Economic Importance): Nematocera and Lower Brachycera / Eds L. Papp, B. Darvas. - Budapest: Science Herald, 1997. - Vol. 2. - P. 71 - 204." type="journal article" year="1997">Skuhravá, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AA8997051FCBEFE3D" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[690,837,367,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 408" refId="ref10317" refString="Gagne, R. J. A catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the world // Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Washington. - 2004. - 25. - P. 1 - 408." type="book chapter" year="2004">Gagné, 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AA9647051FC71FE3D" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[847,906,367,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="2010" refId="ref10356" refString="Gagne, R. J. Update for A catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the world. - 2010. - http: // www. ars. usda. gov / SP 2 UserFiles / Place / 12754100 / Gagne _ 2010 _ World _ Catalog _ Cecidomyiidae. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AA9B87051FB37FE3D" author="Fedotova, Z. A. &amp; Sidorenko, V. S." box="[915,1228,367,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 19" refId="ref10138" refString="Fedotova, Z. A., Sidorenko, V. S. Nine new species of genus Ledomyia Kieffer, 1895 (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) from the Russian Far East // Far Eastern Entomologist. - 2007. - 169. - P. 1 - 19." type="book chapter" year="2007">Fedotova, Sidorenko, 2007</bibRefCitation>
; Fedotova, Perkovsky, 2008). Some undescribed species are known from Middle Miocene Mexican amber (
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AAB447091FDF9FE7E" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[367,514,431,458]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="169 - 171" refId="ref10188" refString="Gagne, R. J. Cecidomyiidae from Mexican Tertiary amber (Diptera) // Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington. - 1973. - 75. - P. 169 - 171." type="book chapter" year="1973">Gagné, 1973</bibRefCitation>
) and Late Eocene Baltic amber, part of species were mistakenly included in extinct genus 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFFCFF8AABF370F1FCECFE5D" authority="Meunier, 1904" authorityName="Meunier" authorityYear="1904" box="[472,791,463,489]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ledomyiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFCFF8AABF370F1FD9EFE5D" box="[472,613,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Ledomyiella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AA84170F1FCECFE5D" author="Meunier, F." box="[618,791,463,489]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="12 - 275" refId="ref11072" refString="Meunier, F. Monographie des Cecidomyidae, des Sciaridae, des Mycetophilidae et des Chironomidae de l'ambre de la Baltique // Annales de la Societe Scientifique de Bruxelles. - 1904. - 28. - P. 12 - 275, pls. I - XVI." type="book chapter" year="1904">Meunier, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, known from Baltic amber. From Late Eocene 
<collectingRegion id="4F78F849FFFCFF8AAB2170CEFEA3FDBE" box="[266,344,496,522]" country="Ukraine" name="Rivne" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Rovno</collectingRegion>
amber was described 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFFCFF8AA87170D1FB8CFDBD" authority="Fedotova et Perkovsky, 2008" authorityName="Fedotova et Perkovsky" authorityYear="2008" box="[602,1143,495,522]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ledomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dextra">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFCFF8AA87170D1FCE5FDBD" box="[602,798,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Ledomyia dextra</emphasis>
Fedotova et Perkovsky, 2008
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D0336ABFFFCFF8AAAC8732EFC59FD3E" blockId="13.[174,1233,175,650]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">
Most of the included species have been reared from fresh-cut logs (
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AA9DA7331FB7CFD9E" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[1009,1159,527,554]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="116 - 134" refId="ref10224" refString="Gagne, R. J. Descriptions of new Nearctic Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) that live in xylem vessels of fresh-cut wood, and a review of Ledomyia (s. str.) // Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington. - 1985. - 87. - P. 116 - 134." type="book chapter" year="1985">Gagné, 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AAEBA7331FB37FD9D" author="Gagne, R. J." box="[1169,1228,527,553]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="2010" refId="ref10356" refString="Gagne, R. J. Update for A catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the world. - 2010. - http: // www. ars. usda. gov / SP 2 UserFiles / Place / 12754100 / Gagne _ 2010 _ World _ Catalog _ Cecidomyiidae. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AAA857311FE60FDFE" author="Rock, E. A. &amp; Jackson D." box="[174,411,559,586]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="135 - 141" refId="ref11383" refString="Rock, E. A., Jackson D. The biology of xylophilic Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) // Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington. - 1985. - 87. - 135 - 141." type="book chapter" year="1985">Rock, Jackson 1985</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFFCFF8AAB9B7311FCD4FDFD" authority="Gagne, 1987" authorityName="Gagne" authorityYear="1987" box="[432,815,559,585]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Ledomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collarata">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFCFF8AAB9B7311FD69FDFD" box="[432,658,559,585]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Ledomyia collarata</emphasis>
Gagné, 1987
</taxonomicName>
was reared from galls on a fungus 
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFFCFF8AAA857371FE1AFDDE" authority="Mont." authorityName="Mont." box="[174,481,591,618]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" genus="Xylaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="enterogena">
<emphasis id="BFC8EAB9FFFCFF8AAA857371FE75FDDD" box="[174,398,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="48">Xylaria enterogena</emphasis>
Mont.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4ABC4D28FFFCFF8AABD97371FCDCFDDE" authority=", Ascomycetes" authorityName="Ascomycetes" box="[498,807,591,618]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Xylariaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Xylariaceae, Ascomycetes</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="E92D4B5AFFFCFF8AA96A7371FBE5FDDE" author="Larew, H. &amp; Gagne, R. J. &amp; Rossman, A. Y." box="[833,1054,591,618]" pageId="13" pageNumber="48" pagination="502 - 507" refId="ref10663" refString="Larew, H. G, Gagne, R. J., Rossman, A. Y. Fungal gall caused by a new species of Ledomyia (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) on Xylaria enterogena (Ascomycetes: Xylariaceae) // Annals of the Entomological Society of America. - 1987. - 80. - P. 502 - 507." type="book chapter" year="1987">Larew et al., 1987</bibRefCitation>
); its adults are unknown and the species is only tentatively placed in this genus.
</paragraph>
